&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Senior Healthcare Assistant - 27.5 hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our Community services development, we are looking to recruit a Band 3 Senior Community Rehab Assistant to join and support our Community hub in Guildford and Waverley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about supporting patients at home, avoiding unnecessary hospital admissions and supporting earlier discharges for those who have required a hospital stay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have previous experience as a Community Rehab assistant in health or Social care, have excellent communication skills and an interest in rehabilitation we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Intermediate care team which includes Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists, Nurses, Community Rehab assistants and Social care staff provides assessment, care and short term rehabilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported with training and career development opportunities which include a team competency program .You will have the opportunity to develop your expertise in a community setting with patients with a range of conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you would like to discuss this vacancy or for further information please contact Shirley Young or Hannah Bowman on 01483 782644.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
